        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 7:11PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 710 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Ellijay, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Jasper, Ellijay, East Ellijay, Talking Rock, Amicalola Falls State
Park, Sequoyah Lake, Talona, Tails Creek, Springer Mountain Shelter,
Len Foote Hike Inn, Cartecay, Pisgah, Black Gap Shelter, Cherry Log,
Mountaintown, Stover Creek Shelter, Roy, and Roundtop.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
